cts and crises that are currently unfolding in the region. As Kamrava demonstrates, each state in the region, including Saudi Arabia, Iran, and Qatar, has embarked on vigorous security-producing efforts as part of foreign policy, flooding the area with more munitions-thereby increasing insecurity and causing more mistrust in a part of the world that needs no more tension.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Nov 2019) 0aHuman securityzPersian Gulf Region. 0aSecurity, InternationalzPersian Gulf Region. 4aInternational Studies. 4aMiddle East Studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package 2018z978311066747908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell Univ. Press eBook-Package Pilot Project 2018z978311060655308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics and Social Sciences 2018 Englishz978311060401608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2018z9783110603231oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501720369zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501720369.jpg  a978-3-11-060401-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics and Social Sciences 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060655-3  Cornell Univ. Press eBook-Package Pilot Project 2018b2018  a978-3-11-066747-9  COR eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME 